  <summary>&lt;p>Minimalistic Splash Screen of Fedora Linux for KDE Plasma 6 .&lt;br />&lt;br />To Install :&lt;br />&lt;br />1 ) Extract the archive to get a folder named '' Fedora-Minimalistic '' .&lt;br />&lt;br />2 ) Copy the folder and paste it inside " ~/.local/share/plasma/look-and-feel " ( no root access required ) or " /usr/share/plasma/look-and-feel " ( root access required ) . If you dont have these folders, then create them.&lt;br />&lt;br />3 ) Head over to System Settings &amp;gt; Appearance &amp;amp; Style &amp;gt; Colors &amp;amp; Themes &amp;gt; Global Theme &amp;gt; Splash Screen &amp;amp; select '' Fedora-Minimalistic " .&lt;br />&lt;br />3.1 ) Alternatively, the Splash Screen can be applied from System Settings &amp;gt; Quick Settings &amp;gt; More Appearance Settings &amp;gt; Splash Screen &amp;gt; Select Desired Splash Screen ( in this case it is " Fedora-Minimalistic " ) .&lt;br />&lt;br />4 ) Enjoy !&lt;br />&lt;br />This project is based on Riyadul Mollick's Fedora Splash Screen.&lt;br />This project has been upgraded to support Plasma 6 and loading animation has been changed.&lt;br />&lt;br />Reach out to me for any queries regarding this on Discord [ freezykaif ] !&lt;/p></summary>
